# Frontmatter Examples in Zolt

This file serves as an index to test various Frontmatter features (YAML metadata) in Zolt. Click the links below to test each scenario individually.

## Basic Examples
- [Basic Configuration](frontmatter/basic.zlt) — Simple title, author, and date.
- [Complete Example](frontmatter/complete.zlt) — Using all standard fields (tags, description, version, etc.).
- [Variable Usage](frontmatter/variables.zlt) — How to inject frontmatter values into the content.

## Specific Metadata
- [Blog Post](frontmatter/metadata-blog.zlt) — Categories, cover images, and "featured" status.
- [Open Source Project](frontmatter/project.zlt) — GitHub repository, license, and contributors.

## Logic and Conditions
- [Theme Selection](frontmatter/conditional-theme.zlt) — Style change based on a variable.
- [Themes and Colors](themes.zlt) — Complete index of built-in themes and Light/Dark modes.
- [Feature Flags](frontmatter/conditional-features.zlt) — Conditional display of sections (comments, search, etc.).

## Advanced Content Management
- [Multiple Authors](frontmatter/authors.zlt) — Iterating over a list of authors with roles and emails.
- [Version Management](frontmatter/versioning.zlt) — Change history (changelog) structured in YAML.
- [Localization](frontmatter/localization.zlt) — Language, locale, and text direction.
- [Multi-language](frontmatter/advanced-multi-lang.zlt) — List of files by language.
- [Document Series](frontmatter/advanced-series.zlt) — Navigation between tutorial parts.
- [Custom Fields](frontmatter/custom-fields.zlt) — Defining metadata specific to your needs (difficulty, duration, etc.).

## Common Patterns
- [API Documentation](frontmatter/patterns-api.zlt) — Typical configuration for an API (base URL, auth, etc.).

## Document Configuration
- [Rendering Parameters](frontmatter/config.zlt) — Control over TOC, numbering, and highlighting.

